.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype female: A. mesosoma, lateral view; B. mesoscutum; C. propodeum;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1951,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="147">D. head, frontal view; E. head, dorsal view; F. head, lateral view; G. hind trochantellus; scale bar = 1 mm, except scale bar for G = 0.5 mm</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="148" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,474,151,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" reason="1">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[370,470,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Head with FI = 0.67, GOI = 3.4, ECI = 0.7. Antenna with 72 flagellomeres, first flagellomere 4.3× longer than wide, 1.8× length of second, 20 
<superScript attach="left" box="[749,761,186,200]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">th</superScript>
flagellomere 1.8× as long as wide; lower face 0.65× as wide as high, mat, with small punctures, pubescent; clypeus 1.6× as wide as high, separated from face by weak impression; malar space short, about 0.3× mandibular basal width (
<figureCitation box="[670,755,259,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-23@5.[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stauropoctonus inaequalis sp. nov., holotype female: A. mesosoma, lateral view; B. mesoscutum; C. propodeum; D. head, frontal view; E. head, dorsal view; F. head, lateral view; G. hind trochantellus; scale bar = 1 mm, except scale bar for G = 0.5 mm" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); occipital carina completely absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
Mesosoma. Pronotum subpolished, densely finely punctate, except ventral wrinkled area, epomia absent; mesoscutum about 1.5× as long as its maximum width, mat, with dense setae; scutellum strongly convex, with coarse punctures, dense setae, with lateral carina present basally, with strong winkles posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1085,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-23@5.[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stauropoctonus inaequalis sp. nov., holotype female: A. mesosoma, lateral view; B. mesoscutum; C. propodeum; D. head, frontal view; E. head, dorsal view; F. head, lateral view; G. hind trochantellus; scale bar = 1 mm, except scale bar for G = 0.5 mm" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); epicnemial carina weakly present on ventral half, upper end turning towards anterior margin; mesopleuron subpolished, with fine punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1424,403,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-23@5.[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stauropoctonus inaequalis sp. nov., holotype female: A. mesosoma, lateral view; B. mesoscutum; C. propodeum; D. head, frontal view; E. head, dorsal view; F. head, lateral view; G. hind trochantellus; scale bar = 1 mm, except scale bar for G = 0.5 mm" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); mesosternum with posterior transverse carina complete but weak medially (
<figureCitation box="[957,1041,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,967,991]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,524,943]" captionTargetId="figure-191@6.[151,1436,524,943]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Mesosternum of Vietnamese Stauropoctonus: A. S. aurantiacus Shimizu &amp; Lima; B. S. inaequalis sp. nov.; scale bar = 1 mm" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
); metapleuron densely punctate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-23@5.[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stauropoctonus inaequalis sp. nov., holotype female: A. mesosoma, lateral view; B. mesoscutum; C. propodeum; D. head, frontal view; E. head, dorsal view; F. head, lateral view; G. hind trochantellus; scale bar = 1 mm, except scale bar for G = 0.5 mm" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); propodeum with anterior area striated, spiracular area coriaceous, pubescent (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1118,475,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-23@5.[154,1433,181,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stauropoctonus inaequalis sp. nov., holotype female: A. mesosoma, lateral view; B. mesoscutum; C. propodeum; D. head, frontal view; E. head, dorsal view; F. head, lateral view; G. hind trochantellus; scale bar = 1 mm, except scale bar for G = 0.5 mm" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="6" pageNumber="148" startId="6.[151,250,967,991]" targetBox="[151,1436,524,943]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,967,1027]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,967,991]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
Mesosternum of Vietnamese 
<taxonomicName box="[578,736,967,990]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Stauropoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[578,736,967,990]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Stauropoctonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: A. 
<taxonomicName authority="Shimizu &amp; Lima" authorityName="Shimizu &amp; Lima" authorityYear="2017" box="[779,1107,967,991]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Stauropoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantiacus">
<emphasis box="[779,926,967,991]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">S. aurantiacus</emphasis>
Shimizu &amp; Lima
</taxonomicName>
; B. 
<taxonomicName authority="Pham &amp; Matsumoto &amp; Cao &amp; Shimizu, 2022" authorityName="Pham &amp; Matsumoto &amp; Cao &amp; Shimizu" authorityYear="2022" box="[1147,1278,967,991]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Stauropoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1147,1278,967,991]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">S. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1284,1365,967,991]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1284,1365,967,991]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; scale bar = 1 mm
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
Wings (
<figureCitation box="[282,419,1075,1099]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[194,1394,185,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-23@3.[194,1394,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Wings, morphological terms and measurement characters of Vietnamese Stauropoctonus: A. Fore wing of S.aurantiacus Shimizu &amp; Lima (DS = discosubmarginal cell, FS = first subdiscal cell); B. hind wing of S.aurantiacus Shimizu &amp; Lima; C. Central part of fore wing of S. inaequalis sp. nov. (AI = cd/ab, CI = gf/fh, DI = k/fe, ICI = ab/cb, SDI = fe/ig, SI =" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Figs 2C, 2D</figureCitation>
). Fore wing length ca. 19.0 mm with AI = 0.67, CI = 0.84, DI= 0.55, ICI = 1.1, SDI = 0.94, SI = 0.26, SRI = 0.42, vein 
<emphasis box="[426,536,1111,1135]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">1m-cu&amp;M</emphasis>
sinuate, vein 
<emphasis box="[689,750,1111,1135]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">1cu-a</emphasis>
opposite 
<emphasis box="[857,929,1111,1134]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">M&amp;RS</emphasis>
, postero-distal corner of second discal cell ca. 90°, postero-distal corner of subbasal cell ca. 40°. Hind wing with NI = 1.2, BCI = 0.61, left hind wing vein 
<emphasis box="[1315,1348,1147,1170]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">RA</emphasis>
with 10 hamuli, right one with 11 hamuli.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Legs. Hind coxa about 2.4× as long as its maximum width, hind femur 0.7× as long as hind tibia, hind basitarsus 2.2× as long as second tarsomere, hind fourth tarsomere 3.2× as long as wide.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" box="[199,1383,1291,1315]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Metasoma with PI = 3, DMI = 1.2, LMI = 4.3, THI = 2.8; T1 with straight petiole; T2 with elongate thyridium.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Colour. Reddish yellow with black markings on interocellar area and median part of T3 dorsally; mesoscutum with three brown stripes, T5 onwards brown; wing veins reddish brown to black, pterostigma reddish.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
Variations. Female 
<typeStatus box="[407,509,1399,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">paratypes</typeStatus>
have antenna with 72–74 flagellomeres, first flagellomere 4.0–4.5× longer than wide, 20 
<superScript attach="left" box="[178,190,1433,1447]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">th</superScript>
flagellomere 1.8–1.9× as long as wide; lower face 0.63–0.67× as wide as high; the fore wing length from 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9149999999999998" metricValueMax="1.95" metricValueMin="1.88" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" unit="mm" value="19.15" valueMax="19.5" valueMin="18.8">18.8–19.5 mm</quantity>
with AI = 0.7–0.8, DI= 0.53–0.55, ICI = 1.1–1.2, SDI = 0.94–0.96, SI = 0.24–0.26, SRI = 0.40–0.45; hind wing with NI = 1.1–1.3, hind wing vein 
<emphasis box="[467,499,1507,1530]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">RA</emphasis>
with 9–11. The female 
<typeStatus box="[751,843,1507,1531]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">paratype</typeStatus>
from Bat Xat Nature Reserve has three black stripes on mesoscutum and its mesosternum with black markings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" box="[199,380,1579,1603]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,424,1615,1639]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" reason="1">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
In 
<bibRefCitation author="Shimizu, S. &amp; Lima, A. R." box="[465,732,1615,1639]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" pagination="34 - 47" refId="ref4578" refString="Shimizu, S. &amp; Lima, A. R. (2017) Taxonomic revision of the genus Stauropoctonus Brauns, 1889 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Ophioninae) in Japan. Entomological Science, 21 (1), 34 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / ens. 12279" type="journal article" year="2017">Shimizu &amp; Lima (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, the new species keys to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gauld, 1977" authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="1977" box="[1015,1408,1615,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Stauropoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torresi">
<emphasis box="[1015,1260,1615,1639]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Stauropoctonus torresi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld, I. D." box="[1270,1408,1615,1639]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref4169" refString="Gauld, I. D. (1977) A review of the Ophioninae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) of Australia. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series No. 49, 1 - 112. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 049" type="book chapter" year="1977">Gauld, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from the latter in its entirely reddish antenna, and the punctate metapleuron. In addition, the new species has the posterior transverse carina of mesosternum complete but weak medially.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1278,1723,1747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" box="[199,1278,1723,1747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1723,1747]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named derived from the posterior transverse carina of its mesosternum unevenly strong.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="149" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1075,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,346,1759,1783]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
Currently known only from montane evergreen forest at elevation from 
<quantity box="[1122,1269,1759,1783]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.68" metricValueMax="1.8399999999999999" metricValueMin="1.52" pageId="6" pageNumber="148" unit="m" value="1680.0" valueMax="1840.0" valueMin="1520.0">1520–1840 m</quantity>
of 
<collectingRegion box="[1305,1391,1759,1783]" country="Vietnam" name="Lao Cai" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Lao Cai</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,249,1795,1819]" country="Vietnam" name="Lai Chau" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Lai Chau</collectingRegion>
provinces, Northwest 
<collectingCountry box="[491,581,1795,1819]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="148">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,176]" box="[151,1437,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">
The new species can be inserted in the key to the world species of 
<taxonomicName box="[853,1019,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Stauropoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[853,1019,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">Stauropoctonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shimizu, S. &amp; Lima, A. R." box="[1059,1314,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149" pagination="34 - 47" refId="ref4578" refString="Shimizu, S. &amp; Lima, A. R. (2017) Taxonomic revision of the genus Stauropoctonus Brauns, 1889 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Ophioninae) in Japan. Entomological Science, 21 (1), 34 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / ens. 12279" type="journal article" year="2017">Shimizu &amp; Lima (2017)</bibRefCitation>
as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1438,219,505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">
3. Posterior transverse carina of mesosternum complete (except weak medially in case of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pham &amp; Matsumoto &amp; Cao &amp; Shimizu" authorityYear="2022" box="[1048,1172,219,240]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Stauropoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
S. 
<emphasis box="[1072,1172,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Laterotergite of T2 folded beneath tergites. Australasian, Oriental, and Palaearctic....................................................... 4
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1438,219,505]" box="[151,1436,277,299]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">- Posterior transverse carina of mesosternum incomplete. Laterotergite of T2 pendant. Neotropical...................... 7</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1438,219,505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">
6. Postero-distal corner of subbasal cell of fore wing 50– 
<superScript attach="none" box="[748,778,306,328]" fontSize="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">800</superScript>
. Fore wing CI = 0.5–0.7. Australasian, Oriental and Palaearctic......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gravenhorst, 1829)" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[1077,1436,336,358]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombycivorus">
<emphasis box="[1077,1236,336,357]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">S. bombycivorus</emphasis>
(Gravenhorst, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1438,219,505]" box="[151,1438,365,387]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">
- Postero-distal corner of subbasal cell of fore wing 40– 
<superScript attach="none" box="[748,778,365,387]" fontSize="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">450</superScript>
. Fore wing CI = 0.8–1.1.................................6’
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1438,219,505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">
6’ Posterior transverse carina of mesosternum complete and entirely strong. Antenna blackish, distally slightly orange. Metapleuron coarsely wrinkled to reticulate. Australasian and Oriental.................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Gauld, 1977" authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="1977" box="[1224,1436,424,446]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Stauropoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torresi">
<emphasis box="[1224,1311,424,446]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">S. torresi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld, I. D." box="[1318,1436,424,446]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref4169" refString="Gauld, I. D. (1977) A review of the Ophioninae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) of Australia. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series No. 49, 1 - 112. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 049" type="book chapter" year="1977">Gauld, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1438,219,505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="149">
- Posterior transverse carina of mesosternum complete but weak medially. Antenna entirely reddish. Metapleuron punctate. Oriental (
